{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Add --concurrency flag for parallel iteration execution using Promise.race pool with no external dependencies","detail":"Simple Promise.race concurrency pool in the orchestrator loop. At concurrency=1, behavior is identical to the previous sequential for loop. At concurrency=2, wall time halves to ~29 hours. No external dependencies (p-limit, p-queue) — the pool is 8 lines of code. Resume support preserved: completed iteration keys are tracked and skipped regardless of execution order. State persistence (collector.savePartialRunState) is serialized by the JS event loop since each processIteration awaits its own persistence calls.","tags":["architecture"],"scope":"src/runner/orchestrator.ts","agent_id":"main","id":"01KM27X89NQPJB11BXGB4N9927","timestamp":"2026-03-19T05:08:20.917Z"}
