{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Fix architecture-cascade scoring: pattern-group detection for decisionPropagation + new decisionDiscovery metric","detail":"Two fixes: (1) Split patterns into EventBus and CallbackRegistry groups, detect which A chose, check if B/C followed that specific choice. (2) Add decisionDiscovery metric measuring whether B/C read A's files and used coordination tools before writing — directly measures Twining's value proposition. Composite weights: propagation 0.3, discovery 0.2, consistency 0.25, quality 0.25.","tags":["implementation"],"scope":"src/scenarios/architecture-cascade.ts","agent_id":"benchmark-runner","id":"01KKKC43NM7745CQT39JSF8XMZ","timestamp":"2026-03-13T10:33:23.380Z"}
{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Smooth bug-investigation resolution scoring to partial-credit gradient (0/15/30/50/70/85)","detail":"Replaced the additive chunk model with a 6-level ordinal gradient: 0 (no investigation), 15 (investigated but no edit), 30 (modified bug file, fix pattern missing), 50 (fix pattern matches, no test), 70 (fix + test but anti-pattern present), 85 (full fix + test + no anti-pattern). This produces a continuous distribution that separates partial progress from complete failures, and rewards the investigation step that was previously invisible to the scorer.","tags":["implementation"],"scope":"src/scenarios/bug-investigation.ts","agent_id":"scoring-improver","id":"01KKNEEHH52VFE0FRDK8V146QP","timestamp":"2026-03-14T05:52:31.269Z"}
{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Add computeCoordinationLift() protected method to BaseScenario using evaluateStandaloneQuality()","detail":"Implementing as a protected method on BaseScenario gives all scenario subclasses access without duplication. The method returns undefined when no evaluator client is present (LLM judging is optional), wraps errors in try/catch (non-fatal), and delegates to the already-implemented evaluateStandaloneQuality() and buildEvaluationContextFromResults() in llm-judge.ts. This keeps scoring orchestration in the scenario layer while keeping evaluation logic in the analyzer layer.","tags":["implementation"],"scope":"src/scenarios/scenario.interface.ts","agent_id":"feature-builder-task3","id":"01KKNENHCQ56JX03NZK7J94YQ6","timestamp":"2026-03-14T05:56:20.503Z"}
{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Implement evolving-requirements as a 4-session scenario measuring mid-stream requirement change adaptation","detail":"4 scoring dimensions with composite weights summing to 1.0: requirementAdaptation (0.30) checks session 3 diffs for priority router + patterns; decisionEvolution (0.25) checks coordination tool calls in session 3 and early discovery by session 4; backwardCompatibility (0.25) starts at 100 and deducts for channel file damage; integrationCompleteness (0.20) checks session 4 for audit service, preferences service, and integration tests. excludeFromAll=true for cost control. Calls computeCoordinationLift() when evaluatorClient is available.","tags":["implementation"],"scope":"src/scenarios/evolving-requirements.ts","agent_id":"scenario-implementer","id":"01KKNF0ANVNYD4BFB1JGXKWD73","timestamp":"2026-03-14T06:02:14.075Z"}
{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Implement iterative-feature-build as a 5-session scenario measuring layered analytics build consistency","detail":"5 scoring dimensions with composite weights summing to 1.0: architecturalDrift (0.30) checks session 5 diffs for imports from analytics models/service and verifies session 1 type names appear in session 5 test imports, penalising model redefinition; layerIntegrity (0.25) checks each layer imports only from its direct dependency (controller→service, service→repository, repository→models) and penalises cross-layer violations; decisionAccumulation (0.25) measures whether sessions 2-5 use coordination tool calls and read prior sessions' output files in the first 30% of their tool calls; integrationCompleteness (0.20) checks session 5 for integration tests importing from analytics controller/service plus audit and rate-limiting patterns. excludeFromAll=true for cost control. Calls computeCoordinationLift() when evaluatorClient is available.","tags":["implementation"],"scope":"src/scenarios/iterative-feature-build.ts","agent_id":"task6-scenario-implementer","id":"01KKNFC9QNRKJTYXJ86J48EXMW","timestamp":"2026-03-14T06:08:46.325Z"}
{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Add CoordinationLift as 11th analysis dimension — the core metric for Twining benchmarks","detail":"CoordinationLift directly answers \"does coordination help?\" which is the benchmark's raison d'etre. Without it, the analysis package would miss the primary signal. Added as Task 9g with full implementation including pairwise lift, per-scenario breakdown, per-dimension breakdown, and summary with significance testing.","tags":["architecture"],"scope":"docs/superpowers/plans/2026-03-14-python-analysis-package.md","agent_id":"main","id":"01KKNPQ0B3PJ1S9FVZNTKRBR1M","timestamp":"2026-03-14T08:16:57.187Z"}
{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Load coordination-artifacts.json alongside transcripts via SessionData wrapper","detail":"Introduced SessionData dataclass pairing transcript + optional artifacts. load_sessions() replaces load_transcripts() as primary loader. BenchmarkRun gains session_data field. This enables the coordination analyzer to measure Twining state growth and entity/decision counts per session.","tags":["architecture"],"scope":"docs/superpowers/plans/2026-03-14-python-analysis-package.md","agent_id":"main","id":"01KKNPQ7CQMV7H66EQPSYHKSBD","timestamp":"2026-03-14T08:17:04.407Z"}
{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Classify persistent-history as coordinated, claude-md-only as uncoordinated for CoordinationLift analysis","detail":"The benchmark measures whether coordination mechanisms improve multi-agent outcomes. persistent-history actively passes context between agents (coordination). claude-md-only is static project config that doesn't change between sessions (not coordination). file-reload-generic was also missing and clearly coordinated.","tags":["architecture"],"scope":"docs/superpowers/plans/2026-03-14-python-analysis-package.md","agent_id":"main","id":"01KKNPWHA6V3D6SGYARYYTBJPG","timestamp":"2026-03-14T08:19:58.407Z"}
{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Add 5 research-grade analyzers + harness summary matrix (Chunk 3) for harness comparison and benchmark validation","detail":"Added 6 new components: behavior_outcome (correlates coordination behaviors with scores), effect_decomposition (attributes lift to specific mechanisms), learning_curve (session-order trends), interactions (scenario × condition interaction effects with disordinal detection), construct_validity (scorer reliability, dimension intercorrelation), harness_summary (single comparison matrix). These transform the package from benchmark reporter to research tool. All are data-driven and handle arbitrary scenario/condition combinations.","tags":["architecture"],"scope":"docs/superpowers/plans/2026-03-14-python-analysis-package.md","agent_id":"main","id":"01KKNQX6FVFE5FPDXT1FMTZX28","timestamp":"2026-03-14T08:37:48.667Z"}
{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Implement Pydantic models and shared test fixtures for benchmark analysis (Task 2)","detail":"Created models.py with all 16 Pydantic model classes matching the plan exactly (GitChurn, RunMetrics, DimensionScore, ScoredResult, ToolCall, TokenUsage, TurnUsage, SessionTiming, FileChange, SessionTranscript, CoordinationArtifacts, EnvironmentInfo, RunConfig, RunMetadata, EffectSize, ConditionSummary, DimensionAnalysis). Created conftest.py with factory functions (make_score, make_metrics, make_scored_result, make_tool_call, make_transcript) and pytest fixtures (sample_scores: 48 results across 2 scenarios x 8 conditions x 3 iterations, sample_metadata). budgetDollars typed as float per plan correction. All models import cleanly.","tags":["data-model"],"scope":"analysis/","agent_id":"models-implementer","id":"01KKNRKPDDZ5FWE088H8N8S5HF","timestamp":"2026-03-14T08:50:05.869Z"}
{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Normalize analyzer outputs in _run_safe by unwrapping DimensionAnalysis and fixing dict-vs-list data format mismatches","detail":"Fixed at the integration boundary (_run_safe) rather than modifying individual analyzers. This approach: (1) converts Pydantic models via model_dump(), (2) unwraps DimensionAnalysis-shaped dicts by extracting details, (3) is backward-compatible with analyzers that already return flat dicts. Also fixed downstream consumers to handle dict-keyed data structures (coordination.per_condition, scenarios.per_scenario) and corrected field name mismatches (avg_twining_pct vs twining_pct). Added numpy bool and Pydantic/dataclass handling to JSON serializer as safety net.","tags":["implementation"],"scope":"analysis/src/benchmark_analysis/","agent_id":"bug-fixer","id":"01KKNXJYRTGB9KHAZCCVTND64C","timestamp":"2026-03-14T10:17:04.538Z"}
{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Create shared _constants.py module for tool classification, condition sets, and thresholds — eliminates 3-way DRY violations and fixes MCP tool name mismatch","detail":"Single source of truth for all tool/condition/threshold constants. normalize_tool_name() strips MCP prefixes enabling correct matching. All dimension modules now import from _constants instead of defining locally.","tags":["architecture"],"scope":"analysis/src/benchmark_analysis/dimensions/","agent_id":"main","id":"01KKPP91RMC5RFGE0RM8J2A368","timestamp":"2026-03-14T17:28:34.325Z"}
{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Statistical methodology overhaul: Hedges' g correction, fix pseudo-replication, fix CI computation, apply multiple comparison corrections, fix unpaired method agreement","detail":"Applied Hedges' g bias correction, aggregated outcomes to cell means to fix pseudo-replication, switched to Spearman r for count data, computed bootstrap CI of mean difference for EffectSize, paired method agreement by ScoredResult, applied Holm-Bonferroni to all multi-test situations, renamed causal-sounding labels to descriptive ones.","tags":["implementation"],"scope":"analysis/src/benchmark_analysis/","agent_id":"main","id":"01KKPP9B4YD65T8YA5J0K55R70","timestamp":"2026-03-14T17:28:43.934Z"}
{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Calibrate statistical framework for realistic scale using MDES instead of required-N recommendations","detail":"Added minimum_detectable_effect(n) to stats.py. Reframed reliability.py around MDES with design_guidance section. Changed recommendations from alarming \"need N runs\" to actionable \"at your n, only effects ≥X are detectable.\" Marked effect sizes below MDES as inconclusive in terminal/report output. This gives researchers honest, actionable guidance instead of impossible sample size targets.","tags":["architecture"],"scope":"analysis/src/benchmark_analysis/","agent_id":"main","id":"01KKPS2AD0P511MV308VMRN9SS","timestamp":"2026-03-14T18:17:19.520Z"}
{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Bump harness defaultRuns from 3 to 5 iterations per scenario×condition pair","detail":"The 5-iteration default is the sweet spot: realistic cost increase, meaningful power improvement (medium-effect detection at 90%), diminishing returns beyond 5. Observed real effects (d=0.4-0.8) fall in the medium range, making this the right calibration point.","tags":["implementation"],"scope":"src/types/config.ts","agent_id":"main","id":"01KKPS2GQ1EMMDQG6K0FGA2RAZ","timestamp":"2026-03-14T18:17:25.985Z"}
