{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Remove process-based checks from scoreAssumptionHandling — now 3 outcome-only components (30+35+35)","detail":"Replaced 4-component scorer (30+20+30+20) with 3 outcome-only components: (1) session 8 surfaced assumption change in code (+30, kept), (2) session 9 updated preferences model (+35, increased from 30), (3) session 9 implemented multi-channel routing end-to-end (+35, new — checks for channel routing logic, multiple channel types, channel interfaces in diffs). No check references coordination tools or files.","tags":["implementation"],"scope":"src/scenarios/sprint-simulation.ts","agent_id":"main","id":"01KN21MNM8T0TRSPRYHFVPZ7PZ","timestamp":"2026-03-31T13:34:30.024Z"}
{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Remove cross-session overlap penalty from scoreCumulativeRework and filter trivial lines from rework counting","detail":"Two changes: (1) Removed cross-session overlap penalty entirely — overlap without rework is coordination working correctly, and the rework ratio already captures uninformed rework. (2) Added trivial line filter (blank lines, lone braces, imports, comments, JSDoc, coordination artifacts) so only substantive code rework is counted. This should increase spread by removing noise.","tags":["implementation"],"scope":"src/scenarios/sprint-simulation.ts","agent_id":"main","id":"01KN21MY18KRP980CQ966P8M8K","timestamp":"2026-03-31T13:34:38.632Z"}
{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Four-part scorer fix plan: graduate assumptionHandling, redesign finalQuality, broaden decisionConsistency detection, equal composite weights","detail":"Each fix targets a specific measurement failure: (1) assumptionHandling regex matches generic SMS keywords every agent produces — need explicit assumption-conflict language; (2) finalQuality dominated by binary compile/pass checks — add test coverage depth and API consistency sub-scores; (3) decisionConsistency pattern detection too narrow with hardcoded session indices — broaden to multiple signals and dynamic session selection; (4) equal 20% weights once all dimensions have meaningful variance.","tags":["implementation"],"scope":"src/scenarios/sprint-simulation.ts","agent_id":"main","id":"01KN8YSGT8WN8E0GWREHRX9E0Q","timestamp":"2026-04-03T05:59:24.232Z"}
{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Graduate scoreAssumptionHandling: require explicit assumption-conflict language, not just keyword overlap with task output","detail":"Three-component graduated scorer: (1) Session 8 flag (+40 max): strong signal requires explicit assumption-conflict language (assum.*email-only, hardcoded.*email, etc.), weak signal gives only 15 pts for generic preference mentions. (2) Session 9 preferences restructure (+35): checks for structural patterns (channel types, channel arrays) with minimum diff size >100 chars, not just keyword presence in a preferences file. (3) Session 9 routing (+25 max, reduced from 35): requires preference-based routing (preference.*channel + switch/if/forEach patterns), basic multi-channel gets only 10. Total still 100 max but achieving it requires genuinely handling the assumption change.","tags":["implementation"],"scope":"src/scenarios/sprint-simulation.ts","agent_id":"main","id":"01KN8Z1XXF78NHFJ0GHENVQY32","timestamp":"2026-04-03T06:03:59.791Z"}
{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Redesign scoreFinalQualityAutomated: add test coverage depth (0-15) and API surface consistency (0-15), rebalance weights","detail":"Six-component scorer (total 100): (1) Compilation 0-15 (was 0-20), (2) Test pass rate 0-20 (was 0-30), (3) Component completeness 0-20 (was 0-25), (4) Architecture consistency 0-15 (unchanged), (5) NEW test coverage depth 0-15 (test files per component across 7 patterns), (6) NEW API surface consistency 0-15 (file naming conventions, exported types, consistent adapter send() method). Components 5 and 6 are differentiating: coordinated agents writing test files for each component and following consistent naming conventions will score higher than agents that only compile and pass tests.","tags":["implementation"],"scope":"src/scenarios/sprint-simulation.ts","agent_id":"main","id":"01KN9TED739SKS6ARDH373Q1A9","timestamp":"2026-04-03T14:02:40.228Z"}
{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Broaden decisionConsistency pattern detection: multi-signal regexes, dynamic session selection, extracted helper method","detail":"Three changes: (1) Replaced single pattern regex with arrays of 7 event-driven and 5 direct-call signal regexes — a session matches if ANY signal matches, not just one specific regex. (2) Dynamic session selection: iterate ALL sessions after session 1, skip those that don't touch notification-related code (notification|adapter|service.*notify|event.*bus), rather than hardcoded indices. (3) Extracted checkConsistencyAgainstPattern as a private helper method for reuse from multiple code paths. Session 1 pattern detection also broadened — uses signal count comparison (eventScore vs directScore) instead of single boolean regex.","tags":["implementation"],"scope":"src/scenarios/sprint-simulation.ts","agent_id":"main","id":"01KN9TPHJXMZQ1N1DD3SGTEJ6P","timestamp":"2026-04-03T14:07:06.845Z"}
{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Collapse identical mechanism table into a note; render lite_vs_full, per_tool_counts, and never_called in effect decomposition section","detail":"When all mechanism diffs are identical the table is actively misleading — it implies differentiation that does not exist. Collapsing to a single explanatory note and surfacing the actually-informative sub-sections (lite_vs_full delta, per-tool counts, never-called tools) gives researchers the correct picture without noise.","tags":["implementation"],"scope":"analysis/src/benchmark_analysis/reports/","agent_id":"main","id":"01KN9V3D1P9VWRA5WMCPQX15XW","timestamp":"2026-04-03T14:14:08.182Z"}
{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Skip engagement check for non-coordination conditions; distinguish underpowered-large-effect from no-effect in lift recommendation","detail":"Non-coordination conditions (baseline, shared-markdown, claude-md-only) should never be flagged for low engagement — the flag is only meaningful for conditions that are supposed to use coordination tools (full-twining, twining-lite). For the lift check, a large observed effect (d≥0.8) that fails significance due to being below MDES is fundamentally different from a near-zero effect: the former is a power problem (fix: run more iterations), the latter is a value problem (fix: improve coordination). Conflating them misleads the researcher.","tags":["implementation"],"scope":"analysis/src/benchmark_analysis/dimensions/recommendations.py","agent_id":"main","id":"01KN9V4V8KH6S8J9HQKW1PY5HW","timestamp":"2026-04-03T14:14:55.507Z"}
